00:00:05.620 --> 00:00:07.990
So they tell us Susie ran a race.

00:00:07.990 --> 00:00:10.950
She ran five miles an hour, and the

00:00:10.950 --> 00:00:13.890
race took her t hours to complete.

00:00:13.890 --> 00:00:15.950
How long was the race?

00:00:15.950 --> 00:00:18.480
Write your answer as an expression.

00:00:18.480 --> 00:00:20.590
Alright, if we're trying to
figure out the number of miles,

00:00:20.590 --> 00:00:24.290
you'd want to take her speed,
which is in miles per hour,

00:00:24.290 --> 00:00:28.490
so five miles per hour
times the number of hours.

00:00:28.490 --> 00:00:30.550
So the number of hours is t, so

00:00:30.550 --> 00:00:33.250
you can literally just
write that as five t.

00:00:33.250 --> 00:00:35.950
Five t literally means five times t.

00:00:35.950 --> 00:00:37.420
